  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency shelter assistance for IDPs in Baseteen Camp affected by Hawija operations.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM and Canadian Aid Organization for International Society Rehab (CAOFISR) will jointly install shelters and site infrastructure for 1,000 IDPs families in Basateen Camp, as part of shelter response to Hawija Military operations. 

Interventions will include upgrading of existing 1,000 tents and replacement of 47 tents. Also, flooring in the tents will be upgraded to raised bases to ensure adequate winterization. Finally, drainage will be constructed for flood control and roads and residential blocks will be developed.</narrative>
  </description>
